APIs Used
GET : https://api.restful-api.dev/objects/5
POST : https://api.restful-api.dev/objects
PUT : https://api.restful-api.dev/objects/5
DELETE : https://api.restful-api.dev/objects/7

Positive Test Cases

GET – Retrieve existing object details
Expected Status Code: 200 OK
POST – Create a new object (ID auto-generated)
Expected Status Code: 201 Created
PUT – Update existing object details
Expected Status Code: 200 OK
DELETE – Delete existing object
Expected Status Code: 200 OK / 204 No Content

POST Request Body
{
  "name": "Mobile Phone",
  "data": {
    "year": 2024,
    "price": 35000
  }
}

Negative Test Cases

GET with invalid ID – Object not found
Expected Status Code: 404 Not Found
POST with empty request body – Validation failure
Expected Status Code: 400 Bad Request
PUT with invalid ID – Object not found
Expected Status Code: 404 Not Found
DELETE with non-existing ID – Object not found
Expected Status Code: 404 Not Found

Validation
HTTP status codes are validated using Postman Tests.
Response body is verified to ensure correct data or error message is returned.
